  <similarSpecies>
    <comments>There are two other species of closed gentians in our area that may be confused with Gentiana andrewsii var. andrewsii.  Gentiana alba differs by having whitish flowers and completely smooth leaf margins and sepal tips.  Gentiana saponaria has much narrower leaves (&lt; 2 cm wide) with shorter, not long pointed tips, and the free part of the sepals are almost as long as the connected tube portion.  In addition to this variety of G. andrewsii, the more western variety, G. andrewsii var. dakotica, has been found here though it is extremely rare.  The western variety can be distinguished by its better-developed petal tips, which are triangular to rounded and often have a free, pointed tip up to 3 mm long.</comments>
